text_cap_native: Sambal penja, sambal khas sulawesi yang terbuat dari cabe, tomat, dan ikan penja

text_cap_en: A flower farm on top of a mountain in Atok, Benguet with an overlooking view of the Mountain Province. Tourists are seen in the background enjoying the view.
text_cap_native: Isang taniman ng mga bulaklak sa tuktok ng Atok, Benguet na may tanawin ng Moutain Province sa likuran. May mga turistang makikitang pinagmamasdan ang tanawin.

text_cap_en: A bofire on the beach lit by dried coconut palm leaves.
text_cap_native: Pagsisiga ng mga natuyong dahon ng buko, sa tabing dagat.

text_cap_en: A painting of a cathedral on pieces of scrap metal.
text_cap_native: Isang larawan ng simbahan na pininturahan sa napaglumaang mga bakal.

text_cap_en: The San Juanico Bridge, a bridge spanning over 2km long connecting the islands of Leyte and Samar. It is said to have been built by a former president for the love of his life.
text_cap_native: Ang San Juanico Bridge ay isang tulay na kumukonekta sa mga isla ng Leyte at Samar. Itoy sinasabing ipinagawa ng isang dating presidente para sa kanyang pinkamamahal.

text_cap_en: Limestone cave called "Hinagdanan cave" with crystalline water where people can be seen swimming.
text_cap_native: "Hinagdanan Cave" na gawa sa apog at may malinaw na tubig kung saan makikitang may mga lumalangoy na bisita.

text_cap_en: A busy urban street scene with various vehicles, including a red horse-drawn carriage called "kalesa".  A person is pushing a cart loaded with goods. In the background, there is a bell tower from a church.
text_cap_native: Isang abalang kalye sa Quiapo, lungsod na may iba't ibang sasakyan, kabilang ang isang kalesa. May isang tao na nagtutulak ng kariton na may kargang mga paninda. Sa likuran, may isang kampanaryo ng simbahan.

text_cap_en: A box of "Ube Pastillas Hopia" a classic Filipino pastry made from purple yam.
text_cap_native: Kahon ng "Ube Pastillas Hopia" isang karaniwang panghimagas na Pinoy na gawa sa ube.

text_cap_en: A detailed monument featuring a large statue of a man holding a bolo, symbolizing Filipino resistance. Surrounding him are various figures in a relief sculpture, depicting scenes of struggle and unity. The letters "KKK" are prominently displayed, representing the Katipunan, a revolutionary society. The Philippine flag is also part of the artwork, emphasizing national pride.
text_cap_native: Isang detalyadong monumento na may malaking estatwa ng isang lalaking may hawak na bolo, sumisimbolo sa paglaban ng mga Pilipino. Sa paligid niya ay may iba't ibang pigura sa isang relief sculpture, na naglalarawan ng mga eksena ng pakikibaka at pagkakaisa. Ang mga letrang "KKK" ay kitang-kita, na kumakatawan sa Katipunan, isang rebolusyonaryong samahan. Kasama rin sa sining ang watawat ng Pilipinas, na nagbibigay-diin sa pambansang pagmamalaki.

text_cap_en: A market stall with a variety of fruits. In the foreground, there are several green avocados. In the background, other fruits like oranges, mangoes, and watermelons are visible, along with some packaged goods on shelves.
text_cap_native: Isang tindahan sa palengke na may iba't ibang prutas. Sa unahan, mayroong ilang berdeng abokado. Sa likuran, makikita ang iba pang prutas tulad ng mga dalandan, mangga, at pakwan, kasama ang ilang naka-pack na produkto sa mga estante.

text_cap_en: A man standing behind a small mobile ice cream cart attached to a motorcycle. The ice cream called "sorbetes" is sometimes referred to as "dirty ice cream" as it is commonly sold as a street food.
text_cap_native: Isang lalaki na nakatayo sa likod ng maliit karito ng ice cream na nakakabit sa isang motorsiklo. Ang ice cream na ito ay tinatawag na "sorbetes" na minsan ring tinatawag na "dirty ice cream" dahil ito ay kadalasang tinitinda sa kalye.

shan noodles and noodles with melted tofu, this is very famous dish in Shan region

text_cap_native: Isang plato ng palitaw na binudburan ng linga at matamis na sarsa, ito'y nakapatong sa dahon ng saging.

text_cap_en: Yangon University Convocation Hall, The most iconic building on the campus, was completed 1927, and since then has hosted the annual graduation ceremonies (including on the day I took my photographs) and many important speeches.

text_cap_native: Ito ang loob ng isang jeep sa gabi na may konting pasahero.

text_cap_en: Traditional Vietnamese architectural sculptures displayed in a museum, with the historic Hanoi Flag Tower in the background.
text_cap_native: वियतनामी पारंपरिक वास्तुकला की मूर्तियां संग्रहालय में प्रदर्शित, पृष्ठभूमि में ऐतिहासिक हनोई फ्लैग टॉवर।

text_cap_en: Ito ay isang tanawin ng mga templong nakapalibot sa Wat Saket.
text_cap_native: This is an overlooking view of the temple surrounding Wat Saket.

text_cap_en: market stall selling a variety of dried fruits and preserved snacks in colorful packaging.
text_cap_native: बाजार में विभिन्न प्रकार के सूखे फल और संरक्षित स्नैक्स की रंगीन पैकिंग में बिक्री।

text_cap_en: This is an overlooking view of the temples surrounding Wat Saket.
text_cap_native: Ito ay isang tanawin ng mga templong nakapalibot sa Wat Saket.

text_cap_en: A traditional Vietnamese pagoda with intricate architecture, decorated with lanterns
text_cap_native: आधुनिक इमारतों के बीच एक पारंपरिक वियतनामी पगोडा, सुंदर वास्तुकला और लालटेन से सजा हुआ।

text_cap_en: This is a Maiyarap, a statue of a demon inside Wat Po.
text_cap_native: Isa itong Maiyarap, estatwa ng demonyo sa loob ng Wat Po.

text_cap_en: This is the interior of Wat Pho, a world-famous temple in Bangkok.
text_cap_native: Ito ang loob ng Wat Pho, isang bantog na templo sa Bangkok.

text_cap_en: Stir-fried water spinach, one of the home-cooked foods that is often found in Indonesia
text_cap_native: Tumis Kangkung, salah satu makanan rumahan yang sering dijumpai di Indonesia

text_cap_en: This is Muay Thai, Thailand's national sport.
text_cap_native: Ito ang Muay Thai, ang pambansang laro ng Thailand.

text_cap_en: This is Yaowarat, Bangkok's Chinatown, during an overcast day.
text_cap_native: Ito ang Yaowarat, Chinatown ng Bangkok, sa maulap na araw.

text_cap_en: Sambal, a typical Indonesian flavoring food or condiment, has a spicy taste
text_cap_native: Sambal, makanan penyedap ataupun kondimen khas Indonesia berasa pedas

text_cap_en: This is the Reclining Buddha statue in Bangkok.
text_cap_native: Ito ang estatwa ng nakahigang Buddha sa Bangkok.

text_cap_en: This is the interior of a traditional Thai house.
text_cap_native: Ito ang interior ng isang tradisyonal na Thai na bahay.

text_cap_en: Linh Ung Pagoda, a multi-tiered Buddhist temple located in Vietnam.The pagoda is a significant religious and cultural site.
text_cap_native: यह वियतनाम में स्थित लिंह उंग पैगोडा की एक छवि है। यह बहु-स्तरीय बौद्ध मंदिर सुंदर नक्काशियों, मुड़ी हुई छतों और मूर्तियों से सुसज्जित है, जो हरी-भरी वनस्पति और पत्थर की मूर्तियों से घिरा हुआ है। यह एक महत्वपूर्ण धार्मिक और सांस्कृतिक स्थल है।

text_cap_en: This is a golden stupa containing relics of the Buddha.
text_cap_native: Ito ay isang gintong stupa na naglalaman ng mga artepakto ng Buddha.

text_cap_en: A towering statue of the Bodhisattva Guanyin at Linh Ung Pagoda in Da Nang, Vietnam. The serene white sculpture stands on a lotus pedestal.
text_cap_native: दनांग, वियतनाम के लिंह उंग पैगोडा में स्थित बोधिसत्व गुआनयिन की विशाल मूर्ति। यह शांत सफेद प्रतिमा एक कमल के आधार पर स्थित है, जो करुणा और शांति का प्रतीक है।

text_cap_en: These are traditional Thai textiles and cloths.
text_cap_native: Ito ay mga tradisyonal na Thai na tela.

text_cap_en: Two sage statues playing a board game in a cave, symbolizing wisdom and strategy, with an altar in the background.
text_cap_native: गुफा में दो ऋषियों की मूर्तियाँ बोर्ड गेम खेलते हुए, जो बुद्धि और रणनीति का प्रतीक हैं, पीछे एक वेदी है।

text_cap_en: This is an ornate arch featuring the Buddha inside Vinh Trang Pagoda.
text_cap_native: Ito ay isang mapalamuting arko ng Buddha sa loob ng Vinh Trang Pagoda.

text_cap_en: This is an ornate arch featuring the Buddha inside Vinh Trang Pagoda.
text_cap_native: Ito ay isang mapalamuting arko ng Buddha sa loob ng Vinh Trang Pagoda.

text_cap_en: Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum in Hanoi, Vietnam, honoring the revolutionary leader Ho Chi Minh, with guards and wreaths at the entrance.
text_cap_native: हनोई, वियतनाम में हो ची मिन्ह समाधि, जो क्रांतिकारी नेता हो ची मिन्ह को समर्पित है, प्रवेश द्वार पर गार्ड और पुष्पांजलियाँ हैं।

text_cap_en: This is the interior inside Vinh Trang Pagoda.
text_cap_native: Ito ang loob ng Vinh Trang Pagoda.

text_cap_en: The black bronze statue of Tran Vu in Quan Thanh Temple, Ba Dinh, Hanoi, a revered Taoist deity, surrounded by offerings and intricate decorations.
text_cap_native: क्वान थान मंदिर, बा दिंह, हनोई में स्थित ट्रान वू की काली कांस्य प्रतिमा, जो एक पूजनीय ताओवादी देवता हैं, चारों ओर भेंट और सुंदर सजावट से घिरी हुई।

text_cap_en: This is snake wine, a traditional alcoholic beverage of Vietnam.
text_cap_native: Ito ay snake wine, isang tradisyonal na inuming may alkohol ng Vietnam.

text_cap_en: This is Pho, Vietnam's national noodle dish.
text_cap_native: Ito ay Pho, ang pambansang pansit ng Vietnam.

text_cap_en: A golden dragon statue in Hue, Vietnam, symbolizing power and royalty, located in an ancient imperial site.
text_cap_native: ह्यू, वियतनाम में एक स्वर्णिम ड्रैगन प्रतिमा, जो शक्ति और राजसी गौरव का प्रतीक है, एक प्राचीन शाही स्थल पर स्थित।

text_cap_en: This is the Vinh Trang Pagoda.
text_cap_native: Ito ang Vinh Trang Pagoda.

text_cap_en: The Lady Buddha statue at Linh Ung Pagoda in Da Nang, Vietnam, a towering symbol of compassion and protection,.
text_cap_native: द नाग, वियतनाम में लिंह उंग पगोडा की लेडी बुद्ध प्रतिमा, जो करुणा और सुरक्षा का एक भव्य प्रतीक है

text_cap_en: This is the Thich Quang Duc Monument in Ho Chi Minh City.
text_cap_native: Ito ang Thich Quang Duc Monument sa Ho Chi Minh City.

text_cap_en: This is the People's Committee Building in front of Ho Chi Minh Square.
text_cap_native: Ito ang People's Committee Building sa harap ng Ho Chi Minh Square.

text_cap_en: This is a bust of Ho Chi Minh, an iconic leader of Vietnam.
text_cap_native: Ito ay isang estatwa ni Ho Chi Minh, isang bayani ng Vietnam.

text_cap_en: The Guan Yu Shrine in Koh Samui, Thailand, features a 16-meter bronze statue of Guan Yu, symbolizing loyalty and bravery, built by Chinese immigrants over 150 years ago.
text_cap_native: गुआन यू श्राइन, कोह सामुई, थाईलैंड में स्थित है, जहाँ 16 मीटर ऊँची कांस्य प्रतिमा है, जो निष्ठा और वीरता का प्रतीक है, इसे 150 साल पहले चीनी प्रवासियों ने बनाया था।

text_cap_en: This is a Lao style of Banh mi bread.
text_cap_native: Ito ay isang Laos na estilo ng Banh mi na tinapay.

text_cap_en: Wat Sila Ngu Temple in Koh Samui, Thailand, a red sandstone Buddhist temple known for its intricate carvings and cultural significance.
text_cap_native: वाट सिला न्गु मंदिर, कोह सामुई, थाईलैंड में स्थित एक लाल बलुआ पत्थर का बौद्ध मंदिर, जो अपनी जटिल नक्काशी और सांस्कृतिक महत्व के लिए प्रसिद्ध है।

text_cap_en: A Thai dish featuring steamed rice with sweet and sour stir-fried meat, vegetables, and cashew nuts, garnished with herbs.

text_cap_en: Guanyin 18 arm Buddhist Goddess in a temple in Thailand. Guanyin, Goddess of Mercy and Compassion at Temple Wat Plai Leam. Her 18 arms symbolize her ability to reach out and provide help across the world.
text_cap_native: गुआनयिन, 18 भुजाओं वाली बौद्ध देवी, जो थाईलैंड के एक मंदिर में स्थित हैं। गुआनयिन, करुणा और दया की देवी, वाट प्लाई लाम मंदिर में विराजमान हैं। उनकी 18 भुजाएँ इस बात का प्रतीक हैं कि वे दुनिया भर में सहायता पहुँचाने की क्षमता रखती हैं।

text_cap_en: The Petronas Towers (Malay: Menara Berkembar Petronas), also known as the Petronas Twin Towers and colloquially the KLCC Twin Towers, are an interlinked pair of 88-storey supertall skyscrapers in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, standing at 451.9 metres (1,483 feet). From 1996 to 2004, they were the tallest buildings in the world until they were surpassed by the Taipei 101 building. The Petronas Towers remain the world's tallest twin skyscrapers, surpassing the original World Trade Center towers in New York City, and were the tallest buildings in Malaysia until 2021, when they were surpassed by Merdeka 118. The Petronas Towers are a major landmark of Kuala Lumpur, along with the nearby Kuala Lumpur Tower and Merdeka 118, and are visible in many places across the city.
text_cap_native: The Petronas Towers (Malay: Menara Berkembar Petronas), also known as the Petronas Twin Towers and colloquially the KLCC Twin Towers, are an interlinked pair of 88-storey supertall skyscrapers in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, standing at 451.9 metres (1,483 feet). From 1996 to 2004, they were the tallest buildings in the world until they were surpassed by the Taipei 101 building. The Petronas Towers remain the world's tallest twin skyscrapers, surpassing the original World Trade Center towers in New York City, and were the tallest buildings in Malaysia until 2021, when they were surpassed by Merdeka 118. The Petronas Towers are a major landmark of Kuala Lumpur, along with the nearby Kuala Lumpur Tower and Merdeka 118, and are visible in many places across the city.

text_cap_en: Es Pisang Ijo, a type of typical food from the Makassar tribe in South Sulawesi, especially in the city of Makassar. This food is made from the main ingredient of bananas coated with green flour dough.
text_cap_native: Es Pisang ijo, sejenis makanan khas Suku Makassar di Sulawesi Selatan, terutama di kota Makassar. Makanan ini terbuat dari bahan utama pisang yang dibalut dengan adonan tepung berwarna hijau.

text_cap_en: Pallu basa, traditional food of the Makassar tribe, South Sulawesi. Pallu basa is made from the innards (intestines) of cows or buffalo.
text_cap_native: Pallu basa, makanan tradisional Suku Makassar, Sulawesi Selatan. Pallu basa terbuat dari jeroan (isi dalam perut) sapi atau kerbau.

text_cap_en: Es Potong/Es Goreng/Es Tongtong, traditional Indonesian ice cream that is skewered and covered in chocolate
text_cap_native: Es Potong/Es Goreng/Es Tongtong, es krim tradisional Indonesia yang ditusuk dan dilumuri cokelat

text_cap_en: Bogor Presidential Palace, one of the six Presidential Palaces of the Republic of Indonesia which is unique due to its historical, cultural and faunal aspects
text_cap_native: Istana Bogor, salah satu dari enam Istana Presiden Republik Indonesia yang mempunyai keunikan tersendiri dikarenakan aspek historis, kebudayaan, dan faunanya

text_cap_en: UI Store inside Universitas Indonesia Library
text_cap_native: UI Store di dalam perpustakaan Universitas Indonesia

text_cap_en: Chocolate Dadar Gulung is a variation of a traditional Indonesian snack made from a crepe-like wrapper made with flour and cocoa, filled with grated coconut cooked in palm sugar.
text_cap_native: Dadar Gulung Coklat adalah variasi jajanan tradisional Indonesia yang terbuat dari kulit dadar berbahan tepung terigu dan kakao, diisi dengan kelapa parut yang dimasak dengan gula merah.

text_cap_en: Kue Lumpur is a traditional Indonesian cake made from a mixture of flour, coconut milk, potatoes, sugar, and eggs, resulting in a soft texture with a sweet and savory flavor.
text_cap_native: Kue Lumpur adalah kue tradisional Indonesia yang terbuat dari campuran tepung terigu, santan, kentang, gula, dan telur, menghasilkan tekstur lembut dan rasa manis gurih.

text_cap_en: Potato Croquette is a popular Indonesian snack made from mashed potato dough filled with seasoned chicken or minced meat ragout, shaped into oval balls, coated with breadcrumbs, and deep-fried until crispy.
text_cap_native: Kroket Kentang adalah camilan khas Indonesia yang terbuat dari adonan kentang tumbuk yang diisi dengan ragout ayam atau daging cincang berbumbu, dibentuk bulat lonjong, dilapisi tepung panir, dan digoreng hingga renyah.

text_cap_en: Kerupuk is a traditional Indonesian snack made from tapioca flour mixed with additional ingredients like shrimp, fish, or garlic, then dried and deep-fried until crispy.
text_cap_native: Kerupuk adalah makanan ringan khas Indonesia yang terbuat dari adonan tepung tapioka dan bahan tambahan seperti udang, ikan, atau bawang putih, kemudian dikeringkan dan digoreng hingga renyah.

text_cap_en: The process of making a lakkian, a building erected as a place to place a chest
text_cap_native: Proses pembuatan lakkian, sebuah bangunan yang didirikan sebagai tempat untuk meletakkan peti

text_cap_en: Buildings in Sudirman Central Business District (SCBD) at night
text_cap_native: Gedung-gedung di Sudirman Central Business District (SCBD) pada malam hari

text_cap_en: Kentang Balado is a traditional Indonesian dish, particularly from West Sumatra, made of fried potato chunks cooked in balado sauce. The sauce is a blend of red chili, shallots, garlic, and tomatoes, creating a spicy, savory, and slightly sweet flavor.
text_cap_native: Kentang Balado adalah hidangan khas Indonesia, khususnya dari Sumatra Barat, yang terdiri dari potongan kentang goreng yang dimasak dengan bumbu balado. Bumbu balado terbuat dari cabai merah, bawang merah, bawang putih, dan tomat, menghasilkan rasa pedas, gurih, dan sedikit manis.

text_cap_en: Tumis Labu Siam is a simple Indonesian dish made from chayote sautéed with spices such as garlic, shallots, chili, and a hint of shrimp paste.
text_cap_native: Tumis Labu Siam adalah hidangan sederhana khas Indonesia yang terbuat dari labu siam yang ditumis bersama bumbu seperti bawang putih, bawang merah, cabai, dan sedikit terasi.

text_cap_en: Makan Bareng or Makan Liwetan, a tradition of eating together with rice and side dishes arranged on banana leaves or oil paper, then eaten together without using a plate, but directly with your hands
text_cap_native: Makan Bareng atau Makan Liwetan, tradisi makan bersama dengan nasi dan lauk yang disusun di atas daun pisang atau kertas minyak, lalu disantap bersama-sama tanpa menggunakan piring, melainkan langsung dengan tangan

text_cap_en: Tempe Sambal, typical Indonesian home food
text_cap_native: Tempe Sambal, makanan rumahan khas Indonesia

text_cap_en: Various Batiks in a Batik Selling Shop in Jakarta
text_cap_native: Beragam Batik di sebuah Toko Penjual Batik di Jakarta
text_culture_loc: Brunei, East Timor, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore

text_cap_en: Corn Fritters are a popular Indonesian snack made from a mixture of coarsely mashed sweet corn, flour, and spices such as garlic, shallots, celery leaves, and optionally chili.
text_cap_native: Perkedel Jagung adalah makanan ringan khas Indonesia yang terbuat dari campuran jagung manis yang ditumbuk kasar, tepung, dan bumbu seperti bawang putih, bawang merah, daun seledri, serta cabai (opsional).

text_cap_en: Salted Egg is a traditional Indonesian food made from duck eggs preserved by soaking them in a salt solution or coating them with a mixture of salt and ash.
text_cap_native: Telur Asin adalah makanan khas Indonesia yang terbuat dari telur bebek yang diawetkan dengan cara direndam dalam larutan garam atau dilapisi adonan garam dan abu.

text_cap_en: Stadion Utama Gelora Bung Karno (GBK) Jogging Track
text_cap_native: Jogging Track Stadion Utama Gelora Bung Karno (GBK)

text_cap_en: Kayutangan is a historic area in Malang City, East Java, known as a hub of activity during the Dutch colonial era.
text_cap_native: Kayutangan adalah kawasan bersejarah di Kota Malang, Jawa Timur, yang terkenal sebagai pusat aktivitas masyarakat pada masa kolonial Belanda.

text_cap_en: Coto Makassar, a traditional Makassar food consisting of long-boiled beef offal and Burasa, a food made from rice and coconut milk wrapped in banana leaves and flattened
text_cap_native: Coto Makassar, makanan tradisional Makassar yang terdiri dari jeroan sapi yang direbus lama dan Burasa, makanan dari beras dan santan yang dibungkus daun pisang dan dipipihkan

text_cap_en: Masjid Raya Bandung is an iconic mosque located in the heart of Bandung, West Java, at Alun-Alun Bandung.
text_cap_native: Masjid Raya Bandung adalah masjid ikonik yang terletak di pusat Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat, tepatnya di Alun-Alun Bandung.

text_cap_en: Roti Sagon, a traditional Indonesian snack made from grated coconut, sago flour and sugar
text_cap_native: Roti Sagon, jajanan tradisional Indonesia yang terbuat dari kelapa parut, tepung sagu, dan gula

text_cap_en: The Asia-Africa Solidarity Monument is located in Bandung, West Java, commemorating the 1955 Asia-Africa Conference.
text_cap_native: Monumen Solidaritas Asia Afrika adalah monumen yang terletak di Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat, untuk memperingati Konferensi Asia Afrika tahun 1955.

text_cap_en: The Asia-Africa Solidarity Monument is located in Bandung, West Java, commemorating the 1955 Asia-Africa Conference.
text_cap_native: Monumen Solidaritas Asia Afrika adalah monumen yang terletak di Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat, untuk memperingati Konferensi Asia Afrika tahun 1955.

text_cap_en: The Asia-Afrika Road Tunnel is part of Bandung's road infrastructure, with historical significance due to its connection to the Asia-Africa heritage area.
text_cap_native: Terowongan Jalan Asia-Afrika adalah bagian dari infrastruktur jalan di Kota Bandung yang memiliki nilai historis karena terhubung dengan kawasan bersejarah Asia-Afrika.

text_cap_en: Gedung Merdeka is a historic building located on Asia-Afrika Street, Bandung, West Java. It was the venue for the 1955 Asia-Africa Conference.
text_cap_native: Gedung Merdeka adalah bangunan bersejarah yang terletak di Jalan Asia Afrika, Bandung, Jawa Barat. Gedung ini menjadi tempat berlangsungnya Konferensi Asia Afrika pada tahun 1955.

text_cap_en: A photo of the Jalan Braga sign that showcases the iconic nameplate of Jalan Braga, one of the historic streets in Bandung.
text_cap_native: Foto plang Jalan Braga yang menampilkan papan nama ikonik yang menunjukkan Jalan Braga, salah satu jalan bersejarah di Kota Bandung.

text_cap_en: Tugu Maung is an iconic monument in Bandung, West Java, featuring a tiger statue (maung) symbolizing the courage and strength of the Sundanese people.
text_cap_native: Tugu Maung adalah monumen ikonik di Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat, yang menggambarkan patung harimau (maung) sebagai simbol keberanian dan kekuatan masyarakat Sunda.

text_cap_en: Kayutangan at night exudes charm with streetlights illuminating this historic area.
text_cap_native: Kayutangan pada malam hari menawarkan suasana yang penuh pesona dengan lampu-lampu jalanan yang menerangi kawasan bersejarah ini.

text_cap_en: Nasi uduk, a dish made from diaroned white rice steamed with coconut milk, and seasoned with nutmeg, cinnamon, ginger, lemongrass leaves, and pepper, which is popular in Betawi cuisine
text_cap_native: Nasi uduk, hidangan yang dibuat dari nasi putih yang diaron dan dikukus dengan santan, serta dibumbui dengan pala, kayu manis, jahe, daun serai, dan merica, yang populer di hidangan Betawi.[

text_cap_en: Front view of Tongkonan, a traditional house from Toraja
text_cap_native: Tampak depan dari Tongkonan, rumah adat asal Toraja

text_cap_en: Rambu Tuka', a traditional Toraja ceremony carried out to give thanks for various things, such as a new house, harvest, and marriage
text_cap_native: Rambu Tuka', upacara adat suku Toraja yang dilakukan untuk bersyukur atas berbagai hal, seperti rumah baru, hasil panen, dan pernikahan

text_cap_en: Tongkonan, Toraja traditional house and Alang, Toraja rice storage area
text_cap_native: Tongkonan, rumah adat Toraja dan Alang, tempat penyimpanan padi Toraja

text_cap_en: Ayam lalapan is a typical Indonesian dish consisting of fried or grilled chicken served with lalapan (raw vegetables such as cucumber, basil, cabbage and tomatoes) and chili sauce as a complement.
text_cap_native: Ayam lalapan adalah hidangan khas Indonesia yang terdiri dari ayam goreng atau bakar yang disajikan dengan lalapan (sayuran mentah seperti timun, kemangi, kol, dan tomat) serta sambal sebagai pelengkap.

text_cap_en: Bukit Bangkirai is a natural tourist destination in East Kalimantan known for its pristine tropical rainforest and iconic suspension bridge.
text_cap_native: Bukit Bangkirai adalah destinasi wisata alam di Kalimantan Timur yang terkenal dengan hutan hujan tropisnya yang asri dan jembatan gantung ikonik.

text_cap_en: Leuit Hills in Majenang, Cilacap Regency, Central Java Province
text_cap_native: Leuit Hills di Majenang, Kabupaten Cilacap, Provinsi Jawa Tengah

text_cap_en: Piong, a typical Toraja food made from rice and coconut milk cooked in bamboo
text_cap_native: Piong, makanan khas Toraja yang terbuat dari nasi dan santan yang dimasak dalam bambu

text_cap_en: A plate of pempek (Indonesian fish cakes) from Palembang
text_cap_native: Sepiring pempek khas Palembang

text_cap_en: Mie Gacoan, food menu from the Mie Gacoan restaurant, one of the famous noodle restaurants in Indonesia which has many branches
text_cap_native: Mie Gacoan, menu makanan dari restoran Mie Gacoan, salah satu restoran mie terkenal di Indonesia yang memiliki banyak cabang

text_cap_en: Angel's Billabong is a famous natural tourist attraction in Nusa Penida, Bali. It is a natural infinity pool with crystal-clear water formed between rock formations.
text_cap_native: Angel's Billabong adalah salah satu destinasi wisata alam terkenal di Nusa Penida, Bali. Tempat ini merupakan kolam alami dengan air jernih yang terbentuk di antara bebatuan karang.

text_cap_en: Bakso Bakar is an Indonesian variation of meatballs, where pre-cooked meatballs are grilled and coated with a mixture of sweet soy sauce, chili sauce, and spices.
text_cap_native: Bakso Bakar adalah variasi bakso khas Indonesia yang dibuat dengan cara membakar bakso yang telah matang, kemudian dilumuri dengan bumbu kecap manis, sambal, dan rempah-rempah.

text_cap_en: Tutut Jawa, a type of snail that is collected for consumption
text_cap_native: Tutut Jawa, sejenis keong yang dikumpulkan untuk dikonsumsi

text_cap_en: Bakso is a typical Indonesian dish served with meatballs, fried tofu, and rice vermicelli.
text_cap_native: Bakso adalah hidangan khas Indonesia yang disajikan dengan bakso, tahu goreng, dan bihun.

text_cap_en: Es teh manis is a typical Indonesian drink consisting of brewed tea, then cooled with ice cubes and added with sugar to give it a sweet taste.
text_cap_native: Es teh manis adalah minuman khas Indonesia yang terdiri dari teh yang diseduh, kemudian didinginkan dengan es batu dan diberi gula untuk memberikan rasa manis.

text_cap_en: Vietnamese Coffee, a specialty coffee served with condensed milk.
text_cap_native: Kopi Vietnam, kopi khas yang disajikan dengan susu kental manis

text_cap_en: Atuh Beach is a natural tourist destination located in Nusa Penida, Bali.
text_cap_native: Pantai Atuh adalah destinasi wisata alam yang terletak di Nusa Penida, Bali.

text_cap_native: Patung Bung Karno di Blitar adalah patung yang dibangun untuk menghormati Bung Karno, proklamator dan Presiden pertama Republik Indonesia.

text_cap_native: Baju pernikahan adat Jawa terdiri dari busana kebesaran seperti kebaya untuk pengantin wanita dan beskap untuk pengantin pria.

text_cap_en: Baju mantenan is traditional from East Java worn by the bride and groom during a wedding ceremony.
text_cap_native: Baju mantenan adalah pakaian adat Jawa Timur yang dikenakan oleh pengantin pada upacara pernikahan.

text_cap_native: Baju mantenan adalah pakaian adat Jawa Timur yang dikenakan oleh pengantin pada upacara pernikahan.

text_cap_en: Opor ayam is a traditional Indonesian dish consisting of chicken cooked in coconut milk with spices such as lemongrass, bay leaves, turmeric, and candlenuts.
text_cap_native: Opor ayam adalah masakan khas Indonesia berupa ayam yang dimasak dengan santan dan bumbu rempah seperti serai, daun salam, kunyit, dan kemiri.
